CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 19, 1959, pg. A7, reads: "Give to Terman Ave. Home - The Palletto Club, a group of civic-minded women, organized in 1955, made its annual Christmas donation Sunday to the Terman Ave. Home for Children. Mrs. Rose Saunders, president officiated. Twenty-five gifts were presented. Four members, shown with the Terman Ave. girls are, seated left: Mrs. Dorothy Richardson; standing, president, Mrs. Saunders; seated right, Mrs. Mildred Chavis, and standing, Mrs. Rose Peters. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of women and girls, including members of Palletto Club Dorothy Richardson seated on left, Mildred Chavis seated on right and Mrs. Saunders and Rose Peters standing, with Christmas gifts at Terman Avenue Home for Children
